<div id="body-box"></div>
<p class="brief">This web application allows users to track their spending. Users can withdraw, deposit, delete, and edit payments. Our web application intends to help users make smart and conscientious decisions with their money by providing a user-friendly but comprehensive analysis of their spending habits. We want our users to be confident in their personal finance.</p>
<div class="container">
  <h1>{{title}}</h1>
<form class="form-group" id="login-form" method="post" action="/login">
  <div class="form-group">
    <label for="username">Username</label>
    <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter username" name="username" id="username">
  </div>
  <div class="form-group">
    <label for="password">Password</label>
    <input type="password" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter password" name="password" id="password">
  </div>
  <button class="btn btn-dark" type="submit">Log In</button>
</form>

<div class="error">
  {{warning}} 
</div>

<a class="signup" href="/signup">Need to register? Click here to sign up</a>
</div>
</div>